Section 230 and LLMs
--------------------

That leads to one of the most interesting questions of all, prompted by thi=
s section in Brereton=E2=80=99s article:

According to this pros and cons list, the =E2=80=9CBissell Pet Hair Eraser =
Handheld Vacuum=E2=80=9D sounds pretty bad. Limited suction power, a short =
cord, and it=E2=80=99s noisy enough to scare pets? Geez, how is this thing =
even a best seller? Oh wait, this is all completely made up information.

Bing AI was kind enough to give us its sources, so we can go to the hgtv ar=
ticle and check for ourselves. The cited article says nothing about limited=
 suction power or noise. In fact, the top amazon review for this product ta=
lks about how quiet it is. The article also says nothing about the =E2=80=
=9Cshort cord length of 16 feet=E2=80=9D because it doesn=E2=80=99t have a =
cord. It=E2=80=99s a portable handheld vacuum.

I hope Bing AI enjoys being sued for libel.

First a caveat: there is in fact a corded Bissell Pet Hair Eraser Handheld =
Vacuum =E2=80=94 here=E2=80=99s an Amazon link ( https://www.amazon.com/Bis=
sell-Eraser-Handheld-Vacuum-Corded/dp/B001EYFQ28?th=3D1 ) =E2=80=94 althoug=
h the reviews there suggest it has excellent suction power and there don=E2=
=80=99t seem to be any noise complaints. It=E2=80=99s possible that Brereto=
n simply looked at the wrong vacuum =E2=80=94 the Bing results don=E2=80=99=
t say cordless at all =E2=80=94 which kind of makes the point that everyone=
